        <num>214</num>
        <heading>Business Tax Credits</heading>
        <section eId="sec_12_326g">
          <num>12-326g</num>
          <heading>Penalty</heading>
          <subsection eId="12_326g__subsec_a">
            <num>(a)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Any dealer violating any provision of sections12-326ato12-326h, inclusive, shall be fined not more than two hundred fifty dollars for the first offense and not more than five hundred dollars for each subsequent offense.</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="12_326g__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content>
              <p>Any distributor violating any provision of sections12-326ato12-326h, inclusive, shall be fined not more than one thousand dollars for the first offense, not more than five thousand dollars for the second offense, and not more than ten thousand dollars for each subsequent offense, except that, if the violation is of subsection</p>
            </content>
          </subsection>
          <subsection eId="12_326g__subsec_b">
            <num>(b)</num>
            <content>
              <p>of section12-326b, such distributor shall be fined an additional one thousand dollars for each carton of cigarettes sold or bought in violation of said subsection.
